----#include <events.ttslua>
do
Events = {
  onLoad = "onLoad",
  onObjectEnterZone = "onObjectEnterZone",
  onObjectPickUp = "onObjectPickUp",
  onObjectDrop = "onObjectDrop",
  onObjectSpawn = "onObjectSpawn",
}

end
----#include <events.ttslua>
----#include <injections.ttslua>
do
GlobalInjections = {}

local function addInjection(injections_table, event, func)
  if injections_table[event] == nil then
    injections_table[event] = {}
  end
  table.insert(injections_table[event], func)
end

function addObjectInjection(object, event, func)
  if object.events_injections == nil then
    object.events_injections = {}
  end
  addInjection(object.events_injections, event, func)
end

function addGlobalInjection(event, func)
  addInjection(GlobalInjections, event, func)
end

function getObjectInjections(object, event)
  return object.events_injections[event]
end

function getGlobalInjections(event)
  return GlobalInjections[event]
end

local function applyInjections(injections_table, event, ...)
  if injections_table == nil then return end
  if injections_table[event] == nil then return end

  local injections = injections_table[event]
  for _, injection in ipairs(injections) do
    injection(...)
  end
end

function applyGlobalInjections(event, ...)
  applyInjections(GlobalInjections, event, ...)
end

function applyObjectInjections(object, event, ...)
  applyInjections(object.events_injections, event, ...)
end

end

----#include <auto_cloning.ttslua>
do
local cloning_source_tag = "cloning_source"

local function executeCloning(object)
  local clone = object.clone()
  clone.setPosition(object.getPosition())
  clone.addTag(cloning_source_tag)
  object.removeTag(cloning_source_tag)
end

local function cloningInjection(colorName, object)
  if object.hasTag(cloning_source_tag) then
    executeCloning(object)
  end
end

addGlobalInjection(Events.onObjectPickUp, cloningInjection)

end

local boardId = "6008c0"
local boardHalfSize = 300
local nodeInnerRadius = 60.622 / 600.0

local function generateSnaps()
  local board = getObjectFromGUID(boardId)
  local snaps = {}

  for _, node in ipairs(nodes) do
    local x = (node.x - boardHalfSize) / boardHalfSize * -1
    local y = (node.y - boardHalfSize) / boardHalfSize * -1
    local eventSnap = {
      position = {x, 1, y},
      tags = {"event_card", "realization_tocken"}
    }
    table.insert(snaps, eventSnap)

    for index, isForward in ipairs(node.forwardRelation) do
      if isForward then
        local angle = math.pi / 2 + (index - 1) * math.pi / 3
        local deltaX = nodeInnerRadius * math.cos(angle)
        local deltaY = nodeInnerRadius * math.sin(angle)
        local relSnap = {
          position = {x + deltaX, 1, y - deltaY},
          tags = {"relation_element"},
          rotation = {0, (index - 1) * 60, 0},
          rotation_snap = true
        }
        table.insert(snaps, relSnap)
      end
    end
  end

  board.setSnapPoints(snaps)
end

addGlobalInjection(Events.onLoad, generateSnaps)

end

local itemsListsIds = {"bffb9a", "8c9809", "21377d", "d10057", "f8bf5a", "4efcd6"}
local itemMarkerTag = "item_marker"

local points = {
  {x = 41, y = 17.5},
  {x = 52, y = 17.5},
  {x = 63, y = 17.5},
  {x = 41, y = 48.5},
  {x = 52, y = 48.5},
  {x = 63, y = 48.5},
  {x = 41, y = 73.5},
  {x = 52, y = 73.5},
  {x = 63, y = 73.5},
  {x = 108, y = 17.5},
  {x = 107.93, y = 61.5},
}

local halfWidth = 117 / 2.0
local halfHeight = 86 / 2.0
local xOffset = 3
local yOffset = 3
local xMult = (halfHeight < halfWidth) and halfWidth / halfHeight or 1
local yMult = (halfWidth < halfHeight) and halfHeight / halfWisth or 1

local function generateSnapsFor(itemsListId)
  local itemsList = getObjectFromGUID(itemsListId)
  local snaps = {}

  for _, point in ipairs(points) do
    local x = (point.x - xOffset - halfWidth) / halfWidth * -1 * xMult
    local y = (point.y - yOffset - halfHeight) / halfHeight * yMult
    local snap = {
      position = {x, 0, y},
      tags = {itemMarkerTag}
    }
    table.insert(snaps, snap)
  end

  itemsList.setSnapPoints(snaps)
end

local function generateSnaps()
  for _, listId in ipairs(itemsListsIds) do
    generateSnapsFor(listId)
  end
end

addGlobalInjection(Events.onLoad, generateSnaps)

end

do
local handsIds = {"76e9c1", "707d50", "b37d34", "ff8fa7", "64d264", "79cf43"}
local nonevenArtifactTag = "non_event_artifact"
local midDeltaX = 12.45
local midDeltaZ = 0.2
local radius2 = 4.7
local radius1 = 2.71

local function snap(coords, angle)
  return {
    position = {coords.x, 1, coords.z},
    rotation = {0, angle, 0},
    rotation_snap = true,
    tags = {nonevenArtifactTag},
  }
end

local function generateSnapsFor(handId)
  local hand = getObjectFromGUID(handId)
  local pos = hand.getPosition()
  local snaps = Global.getSnapPoints()

  local xMult = (pos.x > 0) and -1 or 1
  local angle = (pos.x > 0) and 90 or -90

  local mid = {
    x = pos.x + midDeltaX * xMult,
    z = pos.z + midDeltaZ
  }
  local left1 = {
    x = mid.x + radius1 * math.sin(math.pi / -6 * 5  * xMult),
    z = mid.z + radius1 * math.cos(math.pi / -6 * 5),
  }
  local left2 = {
    x = mid.x,
    z = mid.z - radius2
  }
  local right1 = {
    x = mid.x + radius1 * math.sin(math.pi / -6 * xMult),
    z = mid.z + radius1 * math.cos(math.pi / -6),
  }
  local right2 = {
    x = mid.x,
    z = mid.z  + radius2
  }

  table.insert(snaps, snap(left2, angle))
  table.insert(snaps, snap(left1, angle))
  table.insert(snaps, snap(mid, angle))
  table.insert(snaps, snap(right1, angle))
  table.insert(snaps, snap(right2, angle))

  Global.setSnapPoints(snaps)
end

local function generateSnaps()
  for _, handId in ipairs(handsIds) do
    generateSnapsFor(handId)
  end
end

addGlobalInjection(Events.onLoad, generateSnaps)

end

local contextTile = "Roll"

local function roll(player_color, position, object)
  self.addForce(vector(0, 20, 0))
  -- Use random generated torgue is wrong way. By unclear reason random generated torgue almost always leads to roll same face.
  changeFace = math.random() > 0.5
  if (changeFace)
  then
  self.addTorque(vector(0.42, 0.16, 0.33))
  else
    self.addTorque(vector(0.52, 0.48, 0.93))
  end
end

function onLoad()
  math.randomseed(os.time())
  self.addContextMenuItem(contextTile, roll)
end

ObjectStates.Name: ScriptingTrigger
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
----#include <counter_zone.ttslua>
do
thickness = 0.125
color = color(0.8, 0.1, 0.1, 1.0)
textId = nil
textSize = 72
valueKey = "denomination"

local function updateValue()
  local objects = self.getObjects()
  local total = 0
  for i, o in ipairs(objects) do
    local value = o.getVar(valueKey)
    local count = o.getQuantity()
    count = (count == -1) and 1 or count
    if value != nil then
      total = total + value * count
    end
  end
  getObjectFromGUID(textId).setValue("" .. total)
end

function onLoad()
  --Make an X above the middle of the table
  local pos = self.getPosition()
  local scale = self.getScale()
  local y = pos.y - scale.y / 2
  local p1 = {pos.x - scale.x / 2, y, pos.z - scale.z / 2}
  local p2 = {pos.x + scale.x / 2, y, pos.z - scale.z / 2}
  local p3 = {pos.x + scale.x / 2, y, pos.z + scale.z / 2}
  local p4 = {pos.x - scale.x / 2, y, pos.z + scale.z / 2}
  local border =   {
      points    = { p1, p2, p3, p4, p1},
      color     = color,
      thickness = thickness,
      rotation  = {0,0,0},
  }
  local existLines = Global.getVectorLines()
  existLines = (existLines != nil) and existLines or {}
  table.insert(existLines, border)
  Global.setVectorLines(existLines)

  local text = getObjectFromGUID(textId)
  text.TextTool.setFontColor(color)
  text.TextTool.setFontSize(textSize)
  updateValue()
end

function onObjectEnterZone(zone, object)
    updateValue()
end

function onObjectLeaveZone(zone, object)
    updateValue()
end

end

----#include <counter_zone.ttslua>
do
thickness = 0.125
color = color(0.8, 0.1, 0.1, 1.0)
textId = nil
textSize = 72
valueKey = "denomination"

local function updateValue()
  local objects = self.getObjects()
  local total = 0
  for i, o in ipairs(objects) do
    local value = o.getVar(valueKey)
    local count = o.getQuantity()
    count = (count == -1) and 1 or count
    if value != nil then
      total = total + value * count
    end
  end
  getObjectFromGUID(textId).setValue("" .. total)
end

function onLoad()
  --Make an X above the middle of the table
  local pos = self.getPosition()
  local scale = self.getScale()
  local y = pos.y - scale.y / 2
  local p1 = {pos.x - scale.x / 2, y, pos.z - scale.z / 2}
  local p2 = {pos.x + scale.x / 2, y, pos.z - scale.z / 2}
  local p3 = {pos.x + scale.x / 2, y, pos.z + scale.z / 2}
  local p4 = {pos.x - scale.x / 2, y, pos.z + scale.z / 2}
  local border =   {
      points    = { p1, p2, p3, p4, p1},
      color     = color,
      thickness = thickness,
      rotation  = {0,0,0},
  }
  local existLines = Global.getVectorLines()
  existLines = (existLines != nil) and existLines or {}
  table.insert(existLines, border)
  Global.setVectorLines(existLines)

  local text = getObjectFromGUID(textId)
  text.TextTool.setFontColor(color)
  text.TextTool.setFontSize(textSize)
  updateValue()
end

function onObjectEnterZone(zone, object)
    updateValue()
end

function onObjectLeaveZone(zone, object)
    updateValue()
end

end

ObjectStates.Name: Deck
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
----#include <data_utils.ttslua>
do
function countArrayWithCondition(array, condition)
  local count = 0
  for _, object in ipairs(array) do
    if condition(object) then
      count = count + 1
    end
  end
  return count
end

function map(table, mapFunc)
    local result = {}
    for k, v in pairs(table) do
        result[k] = mapFunc(v)
    end
    return result
end

function arrayContains(array, value)
  for _, v in ipairs(array) do
    if v == value then return true end
  end
  return false
end

function arraysHaveIntersection(array1, array2)
  for _, v1 in ipairs(array1) do
    for _, v2 in ipairs(array2) do
      if v1 == v2 then return true end
    end
  end
  return false
end

end
----#include <data_utils.ttslua>

local contextTile = "Start a hand refilling"
local notEnoughCardsMessage = "Not enough cards. Please take cards manually, shuffle discarded cards and then take more to get necessary amount - "
local cardsCountForPlayersCount = {[3] = 4, [4] = 3, [5] = 3, [6] = 3}
local spectrator = "Gray"
local master = "Black"

local fillingZonesIds = {
  ["Orange"] = "301832",
  ["Yellow"] = "6870d6",
  ["Teal"] = "55e6e3",
  ["Blue"] = "89e867",
  ["Purple"] = "e83bf4",
  ["White"] = "dbc42d"
}


local function takeCardsRecursively(player_color, index, total)
  local zone = getObjectFromGUID(fillingZonesIds[player_color])
  local cardPosZ = (index + 0.5) / total - 0.5
  local cardPos = zone.positionToWorld({0, 1, cardPosZ})

  self.takeObject({
    callback_function = function(card)
      if not card.isDestroyed() then
          card.setPositionSmooth(cardPos, false)
      end

      if index ~= total - 1 then
        Wait.time( function () takeCardsRecursively(player_color, index + 1, total) end, 0)
      end
    end
  })
end

local function playerValidator(player)
  return player.color ~= spectrator and player.color ~= master
end

local function getRefillingCards(player_color, position, object)
  local playersCount = countArrayWithCondition(Player.getPlayers(), playerValidator)
  local cardsCount = cardsCountForPlayersCount[playersCount]
  cardsCount = (cardsCount == nil) and 3 or cardCount

  if self.getQuantity() >= cardsCount then
    takeCardsRecursively(player_color, 0, cardsCount)
  else
    broadcastToColor(notEnoughCardsMessage .. cardsCount, player_color, Color.Red)
  end
end

function onLoad()
  self.addContextMenuItem(contextTile, getRefillingCards)
end

ObjectStates.LuaScript:
----#include <hand_refilling_zone.ttslua>
do
----#include <events.ttslua>
do
Events = {
  onLoad = "onLoad",
  onObjectEnterZone = "onObjectEnterZone",
  onObjectPickUp = "onObjectPickUp",
  onObjectDrop = "onObjectDrop",
  onObjectSpawn = "onObjectSpawn",
}

end
----#include <events.ttslua>
----#include <injections.ttslua>
do
GlobalInjections = {}

local function addInjection(injections_table, event, func)
  if injections_table[event] == nil then
    injections_table[event] = {}
  end
  table.insert(injections_table[event], func)
end

function addObjectInjection(object, event, func)
  if object.events_injections == nil then
    object.events_injections = {}
  end
  addInjection(object.events_injections, event, func)
end

function addGlobalInjection(event, func)
  addInjection(GlobalInjections, event, func)
end

function getObjectInjections(object, event)
  return object.events_injections[event]
end

function getGlobalInjections(event)
  return GlobalInjections[event]
end

local function applyInjections(injections_table, event, ...)
  if injections_table == nil then return end
  if injections_table[event] == nil then return end

  local injections = injections_table[event]
  for _, injection in ipairs(injections) do
    injection(...)
  end
end

function applyGlobalInjections(event, ...)
  applyInjections(GlobalInjections, event, ...)
end

function applyObjectInjections(object, event, ...)
  applyInjections(object.events_injections, event, ...)
end

end

----#include <data_utils.ttslua>

local selectionTitle = "Take to hand"
local faceUp = {0, 0, 0}
local faceDown = {0, 0, 180}
local eventsTag = "event_card"
local discardedPosition = {-11.7, 1.15, -15.15}
local choosen = nil

local function finishRefilling(player_color, selected)
  choosen = selected
  for _, object in ipairs(self.getObjects()) do
    if object.hasTag(eventsTag) then
      object.clearContextMenu()
      object.setRotation(faceDown)
      if object ~= choosen then
        object.setPositionSmooth(discardedPosition, false)
      else
        choosen.drop()
        choosen.deal(1, player_color)
      end
    end
  end
end

local function handleObject(object)
  if not object.hasTag(eventsTag) then return end
  if object == choosen then return end
  local source = object.getRotation()
  object.setRotation(faceUp)
  object.clearContextMenu()
  object.addContextMenuItem(selectionTitle, function (player_color) finishRefilling(player_color, object) end, bool)
end

function onObjectEnterZone(zone, object)
  log("Enterred: ")
  log(object)
  if object.held_by_color ~= nil then return end
  handleObject(object)
end

function onObjectDrop(_, object)
  log("Dropped: ")
  log(object)
  if arrayContains(self.getObjects(), object) then
    onObjectEnterZone(self, object)
  end
end

function onObjectPickUp(player_color, object)
  if arrayContains(self.getObjects(), object) then
    finishRefilling(player_color, object)
  end
end

end
